{
  "doc_id": "25439",
  "text": "Literature suggests that appropriate alternative in measuring food diversity is to employ the Berry Index [CITATION_1] ). Berry Index has been applied in empirical economic studies to investigate food diversity [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] . Empirical studies based on individual household data so far have been devoted to studying actual consumption behaviour in different countries. For example, [CITATION_4] addressed the demand for a varied diet in an economy in transition. They found out that the length of the time allowed for consumption is an important element in measuring the demand for food diversity.",
